Note:
STREAM - Lazy pull-stream iterator.

A Stream<T> is an iterator that yields values one at a time via a
caller-supplied next-fn. Streams are lazy: values are computed when the
consumer asks for them. This module also provides eager builders
(from_list, from_range), pure transformers (map, filter, take, drop,
flat_map, chain, zip, window, enumerate) and terminal operations
(fold, reduce, collect_to_list, count, any, all, find, for_each).

Stream layout (40 bytes):
  offset 0:  next_fn         (8 bytes) - Process pointer; signature
                                          (state) -> Integer (encoded result)
  offset 8:  state_ptr       (8 bytes) - owning state, freed by destroy_fn
  offset 16: destroy_fn      (8 bytes) - Process pointer to free state_ptr
  offset 24: exhausted_flag  (8 bytes) - 1 once next_fn reports STREAM_END
  offset 32: out_holder      (8 bytes) - scratch slot used by next-fn outputs

next-fn protocol:
  return STREAM_OK and write the next value to out_holder[0],
  return STREAM_END when the stream is exhausted,
  return STREAM_ERROR for an unrecoverable error.

Dependencies:
- memory/layout.runa
- core/memory_core.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Mem

Constant STREAM_OFF_NEXT as Integer is 0
Constant STREAM_OFF_STATE as Integer is 8
Constant STREAM_OFF_DESTROY as Integer is 16
Constant STREAM_OFF_EXHAUSTED as Integer is 24
Constant STREAM_OFF_OUT as Integer is 32
Constant STREAM_STRUCT_SIZE as Integer is 40

Constant STREAM_OK as Integer is 1
Constant STREAM_END as Integer is 0
Constant STREAM_ERROR as Integer is -1
Constant STREAM_ERR_INVALID as Integer is -2

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Indirect-call shims — real x86_64 indirect dispatch via inline assembly.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "stream_runtime_call_indirect_2" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Forwards (state, out_holder) -> Integer via real indirect call.
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a at [rbp-16], b at [rbp-24], result at [rbp-32].
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        mov rsi, qword ptr [rbp-24]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-32], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_runtime_call_indirect_1" takes fn as Integer, a as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Forwards (state) -> Integer via real indirect call.
    Note: fn at [rbp-8], a at [rbp-16], result at [rbp-24].
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov rdi, qword ptr [rbp-16]
        call rax
        mov qword ptr [rbp-24], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Constructor & destructor
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a stream by binding a generator function, an opaque state
pointer and an optional destroy function. The destroy function is
called once by stream_destroy to release state.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate the 40-byte record, populate fields, return the pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One allocation per stream. The state is allocated by the caller.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The next-fn must abide by the next-fn protocol described above.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "stream_create" takes next_fn as Integer, state_ptr as Integer, destroy_fn as Integer returns Integer:
    If next_fn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let s be proc allocate from Memory with STREAM_STRUCT_SIZE
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_NEXT, next_fn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_STATE, state_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_DESTROY, destroy_fn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_EXHAUSTED, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_OUT, 0
    Return s
End Process

Process called "stream_destroy" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let destroy_fn be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_DESTROY
    Let state_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_STATE
    If destroy_fn is not equal to 0:
        proc stream_runtime_call_indirect_1 with destroy_fn, state_ptr
    Otherwise:
        If state_ptr is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Memory with state_ptr
        End If
    End If
    proc deallocate from Memory with s
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "stream_is_exhausted" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_EXHAUSTED
End Process

@Reasoning
Pull a single value from the stream. The caller receives STREAM_OK with
the value written via out_holder, STREAM_END if there are no more
values, or STREAM_ERROR if the generator reported an error.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
If the exhausted flag is already set, immediately return STREAM_END.
Otherwise invoke the next-fn via the indirect shim, passing state and
the stream's scratch out_holder. Mirror the result into the caller's
out_holder and update the exhausted flag.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
One indirect call per pulled value plus two memory stores.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
out_holder must point to writable storage when STREAM_OK is returned.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "stream_next" takes s as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    If out_holder is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let exhausted be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_EXHAUSTED
    If exhausted is equal to 1:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let next_fn be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_NEXT
    Let state_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_STATE
    Let scratch_addr be s plus STREAM_OFF_OUT
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with scratch_addr, 0, 0
    Let rc be proc stream_runtime_call_indirect_2 with next_fn, state_ptr, scratch_addr
    If rc is equal to STREAM_OK:
        Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with scratch_addr, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0, value
        Return STREAM_OK
    End If
    If rc is equal to STREAM_END:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with s, STREAM_OFF_EXHAUSTED, 1
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Return STREAM_ERROR
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Source builders
Note: ============================================================================

Note: --- from_list ---
Note: State layout: [list_ptr, len, cursor]

Constant LIST_STATE_LIST as Integer is 0
Constant LIST_STATE_LEN as Integer is 8
Constant LIST_STATE_CURSOR as Integer is 16
Constant LIST_STATE_SIZE as Integer is 24

Process called "stream_list_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let list_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, LIST_STATE_LIST
    Let len be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, LIST_STATE_LEN
    Let cursor be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, LIST_STATE_CURSOR
    If cursor is greater than or equal to len:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let offset be cursor multiplied by 8
    Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with list_ptr, offset
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, LIST_STATE_CURSOR, (cursor plus 1)
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "stream_from_list" takes list_ptr as Integer, len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let state be proc allocate from Memory with LIST_STATE_SIZE
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, LIST_STATE_LIST, list_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, LIST_STATE_LEN, len
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, LIST_STATE_CURSOR, 0
    Note: We deliberately pass 0 for destroy_fn so the default deallocate runs.
    Return proc stream_create with proc_address_stream_list_next(), state, 0
End Process

Note: Helper that returns the address of stream_list_next. Compiler-resolved.
Process called "proc_address_stream_list_next" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_list_next]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Note: --- from_range ---
Note: State layout: [cursor, end, step]

Constant RANGE_STATE_CURSOR as Integer is 0
Constant RANGE_STATE_END as Integer is 8
Constant RANGE_STATE_STEP as Integer is 16
Constant RANGE_STATE_SIZE as Integer is 24

Process called "stream_range_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let cursor be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, RANGE_STATE_CURSOR
    Let end_v be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, RANGE_STATE_END
    Let step be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, RANGE_STATE_STEP
    If step is greater than 0:
        If cursor is greater than or equal to end_v:
            Return STREAM_END
        End If
    Otherwise:
        If step is less than 0:
            If cursor is less than or equal to end_v:
                Return STREAM_END
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Return STREAM_END
        End If
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0, cursor
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, RANGE_STATE_CURSOR, (cursor plus step)
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_range_next" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_range_next]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_from_range" takes start_v as Integer, end_v as Integer, step as Integer returns Integer:
    Let st be step
    If st is equal to 0:
        Set st to 1
    End If
    Let state be proc allocate from Memory with RANGE_STATE_SIZE
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, RANGE_STATE_CURSOR, start_v
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, RANGE_STATE_END, end_v
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, RANGE_STATE_STEP, st
    Return proc stream_create with proc_address_stream_range_next(), state, 0
End Process

Note: --- from_repeat (infinite repeat of single value) ---
Note: State layout: [value, remaining]  -- remaining < 0 means infinite

Constant REPEAT_STATE_VALUE as Integer is 0
Constant REPEAT_STATE_REMAINING as Integer is 8
Constant REPEAT_STATE_SIZE as Integer is 16

Process called "stream_repeat_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let remaining be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, REPEAT_STATE_REMAINING
    If remaining is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, REPEAT_STATE_VALUE
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0, value
    If remaining is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, REPEAT_STATE_REMAINING, (remaining minus 1)
    End If
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_repeat_next" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_repeat_next]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_from_repeat" takes value as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    Let state be proc allocate from Memory with REPEAT_STATE_SIZE
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rem be count
    If rem is less than 0:
        Set rem to -1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, REPEAT_STATE_VALUE, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, REPEAT_STATE_REMAINING, rem
    Return proc stream_create with proc_address_stream_repeat_next(), state, 0
End Process

Note: --- from_iterate (seed + step_fn) ---
Note: State layout: [cursor, step_fn]

Constant ITER_STATE_CURSOR as Integer is 0
Constant ITER_STATE_STEP as Integer is 8
Constant ITER_STATE_SIZE as Integer is 16

Process called "stream_iterate_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let cursor be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, ITER_STATE_CURSOR
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0, cursor
    Let step_fn be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, ITER_STATE_STEP
    If step_fn is not equal to 0:
        Let next_v be proc stream_runtime_call_indirect_1 with step_fn, cursor
        proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, ITER_STATE_CURSOR, next_v
    End If
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_iterate_next" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_iterate_next]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_from_iterate" takes seed as Integer, step_fn as Integer returns Integer:
    Let state be proc allocate from Memory with ITER_STATE_SIZE
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, ITER_STATE_CURSOR, seed
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, ITER_STATE_STEP, step_fn
    Return proc stream_create with proc_address_stream_iterate_next(), state, 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Transformers
Note: ============================================================================

Note: --- map ---
Note: State layout: [source, fn]

Constant MAP_STATE_SOURCE as Integer is 0
Constant MAP_STATE_FN as Integer is 8
Constant MAP_STATE_SIZE as Integer is 16

Process called "stream_map_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, MAP_STATE_SOURCE
    Let fn be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, MAP_STATE_FN
    Let tmp be 0
    Let tmp_addr be state plus MAP_STATE_SIZE
    Note: We reuse out_holder for the source pull then transform in-place.
    Let rc be proc stream_next with source, out_holder
    If rc is not equal to STREAM_OK:
        Return rc
    End If
    Let original be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0
    Let mapped be proc stream_runtime_call_indirect_1 with fn, original
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0, mapped
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_map_next" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_map_next]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_map_destroy" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_OK
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, MAP_STATE_SOURCE
    If source is not equal to 0:
        proc stream_destroy with source
    End If
    proc deallocate from Memory with state
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_map_destroy" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_map_destroy]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_map" takes source as Integer, fn as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If fn is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let state be proc allocate from Memory with MAP_STATE_SIZE
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, MAP_STATE_SOURCE, source
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, MAP_STATE_FN, fn
    Return proc stream_create with proc_address_stream_map_next(), state, proc_address_stream_map_destroy()
End Process

Note: --- filter ---
Note: State layout: [source, predicate]

Constant FILT_STATE_SOURCE as Integer is 0
Constant FILT_STATE_PRED as Integer is 8
Constant FILT_STATE_SIZE as Integer is 16

Process called "stream_filter_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, FILT_STATE_SOURCE
    Let pred be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, FILT_STATE_PRED
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let rc be proc stream_next with source, out_holder
        If rc is not equal to STREAM_OK:
            Return rc
        End If
        Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0
        Let keep be proc stream_runtime_call_indirect_1 with pred, value
        If keep is not equal to 0:
            Return STREAM_OK
        End If
    End While
    Return STREAM_END
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_filter_next" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_filter_next]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_filter_destroy" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_OK
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, FILT_STATE_SOURCE
    If source is not equal to 0:
        proc stream_destroy with source
    End If
    proc deallocate from Memory with state
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_filter_destroy" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_filter_destroy]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_filter" takes source as Integer, predicate as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If predicate is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let state be proc allocate from Memory with FILT_STATE_SIZE
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, FILT_STATE_SOURCE, source
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, FILT_STATE_PRED, predicate
    Return proc stream_create with proc_address_stream_filter_next(), state, proc_address_stream_filter_destroy()
End Process

Note: --- take(n) ---
Note: State layout: [source, remaining]

Constant TAKE_STATE_SOURCE as Integer is 0
Constant TAKE_STATE_REMAINING as Integer is 8
Constant TAKE_STATE_SIZE as Integer is 16

Process called "stream_take_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let remaining be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, TAKE_STATE_REMAINING
    If remaining is less than or equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, TAKE_STATE_SOURCE
    Let rc be proc stream_next with source, out_holder
    If rc is not equal to STREAM_OK:
        Return rc
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, TAKE_STATE_REMAINING, (remaining minus 1)
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_take_next" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_take_next]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_take_destroy" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_OK
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, TAKE_STATE_SOURCE
    If source is not equal to 0:
        proc stream_destroy with source
    End If
    proc deallocate from Memory with state
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_take_destroy" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_take_destroy]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_take" takes source as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let state be proc allocate from Memory with TAKE_STATE_SIZE
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be count
    If n is less than 0:
        Set n to 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, TAKE_STATE_SOURCE, source
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, TAKE_STATE_REMAINING, n
    Return proc stream_create with proc_address_stream_take_next(), state, proc_address_stream_take_destroy()
End Process

Note: --- drop(n) ---
Note: State layout: [source, remaining_to_drop]

Constant DROP_STATE_SOURCE as Integer is 0
Constant DROP_STATE_REMAINING as Integer is 8
Constant DROP_STATE_SIZE as Integer is 16

Process called "stream_drop_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, DROP_STATE_SOURCE
    Let remaining be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, DROP_STATE_REMAINING
    While remaining is greater than 0:
        Let drop_rc be proc stream_next with source, out_holder
        If drop_rc is not equal to STREAM_OK:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, DROP_STATE_REMAINING, 0
            Return drop_rc
        End If
        Set remaining to remaining minus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, DROP_STATE_REMAINING, 0
    Return proc stream_next with source, out_holder
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_drop_next" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_drop_next]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_drop_destroy" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_OK
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, DROP_STATE_SOURCE
    If source is not equal to 0:
        proc stream_destroy with source
    End If
    proc deallocate from Memory with state
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_drop_destroy" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
        lea rax, qword ptr [rip + streams_stream__stream_drop_destroy]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-8], rax
        .att_syntax prefix
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "stream_drop" takes source as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let state be proc allocate from Memory with DROP_STATE_SIZE
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let n be count
    If n is less than 0:
        Set n to 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, DROP_STATE_SOURCE, source
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, DROP_STATE_REMAINING, n
    Return proc stream_create with proc_address_stream_drop_next(), state, proc_address_stream_drop_destroy()
End Process

Note: --- take_while ---
Note: State layout: [source, predicate, done_flag]

Constant TW_STATE_SOURCE as Integer is 0
Constant TW_STATE_PRED as Integer is 8
Constant TW_STATE_DONE as Integer is 16
Constant TW_STATE_SIZE as Integer is 24

Process called "stream_take_while_next" takes state as Integer, out_holder as Integer returns Integer:
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let done_flag be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, TW_STATE_DONE
    If done_flag is equal to 1:
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, TW_STATE_SOURCE
    Let pred be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with state, TW_STATE_PRED
    Let rc be proc stream_next with source, out_holder
    If rc is not equal to STREAM_OK:
        Return rc
    End If
    Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with out_holder, 0
    Let keep be proc stream_runtime_call_indirect_1 with pred, value
    If keep is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with state, TW_STATE_DONE, 1
        Return STREAM_END
    End If
    Return STREAM_OK
End Process

Process called "proc_address_stream_take_while_next" returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        .intel_syntax noprefix
